- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0001-74757207
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0001
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: non-compliance with Union harmonisation legislation
  conditions:
  - product contains an AI system to which this Regulation and the Union harmonisation
    legislation listed in Section A of Annex I apply
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider shall ensure that their product is fully compliant with all applicable
    requirements under applicable Union harmonisation legislation.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: 'Vague legal obligation: ''full compliance with all applicable Union harmonisation
      legislation'' requires legal judgment and external evidence, not directly verifiable
      via artifacts.'
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-0edbbb5a
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: unmanaged risks to health, safety or fundamental rights
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The developer shall establish, implement, document and maintain a risk management
    system in relation to high-risk AI systems.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Obligation lacks objective criteria or defined artifacts for an automated
      pass/fail check of establishing/maintaining a 'risk management system'.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
    - log_check
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-7689ca18
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: unmanaged lifecycle risks to health, safety or fundamental rights
  conditions:
  - throughout the entire lifecycle of a high-risk AI system
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The developer shall plan and run the risk management system as a continuous iterative
    process throughout the entire lifecycle of the high-risk AI system.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Vague obligation lacking concrete artifacts or measurable criteria; no
      specified observable signal to objectively verify compliance.
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-64b3067a
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: outdated or unreviewed risks to health, safety or fundamental rights
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The developer shall conduct regular systematic review and updating of the risk
    management system.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: No specified frequency, criteria, or required artifacts; cannot objectively
      verify review/update occurred.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - repo_check
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-a0dc4362
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: undetected risks to health, safety or fundamental rights
  conditions:
  - when the system is used in accordance with its intended purpose
  - under conditions of reasonably foreseeable misuse
  - based on data gathered from the post-market monitoring system referred to in Article
    72
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The developer shall ensure the risk management system comprises identification
    and analysis of known and reasonably foreseeable risks to health, safety or fundamental
    rights and the estimation and evaluation of risks, including those emerging under
    reasonably foreseeable misuse, and the evaluation of other risks based on post-market
    monitoring data.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Uses subjective terms ('reasonably foreseeable') and lacks objective pass/fail
      criteria or specified artifacts to verify compliance.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-250808fb
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: unmitigated risks to health, safety or fundamental rights
  conditions:
  - to address the risks identified pursuant to the identification and analysis step
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The developer shall adopt appropriate and targeted risk management measures designed
    to address the risks identified pursuant to the identification and analysis step.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Vague 'appropriate and targeted' lacks objective criteria; no observable
      pass/fail predicate to verify via logs/configs or I/O.
    evidence_signals:
    - config_check
    - repo_check
    - log_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-e071b823
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: consideration of non-mitigable risks
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The developer shall ensure that the risks referred to in this Article concern
    only those which may be reasonably mitigated or eliminated through the development
    or design of the high-risk AI system, or the provision of adequate technical information.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Depends on subjective 'reasonably mitigated' judgement; no objective io/log/config/data/repo/ci
      oracle verifies compliance.
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0003-63112607
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: unacceptable residual risk
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - developer shall ensure that the risk management measures are such that the relevant
    residual risk associated with each hazard, as well as the overall residual risk
    of the high-risk AI systems, is judged to be acceptable.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: No objective acceptance criteria or measurable threshold for 'acceptable'
      residual risk; cannot be verified automatically.
    evidence_signals:
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0003-bc19ed17
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: residual hazards due to inadequate design
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - developer shall eliminate or reduce risks identified and evaluated pursuant to
    paragraph 2, inasmuch as technically feasible, through adequate design and development
    of the high-risk AI system.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Criteria are vague ('adequate design', 'as technically feasible') and
      lack measurable thresholds or an objective oracle for pass/fail verification.
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0003-49282319
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: unmitigated non-eliminable risks
  conditions:
  - for risks that cannot be eliminated
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - developer shall implement adequate mitigation and control measures addressing
    risks that cannot be eliminated.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: No objective criteria for what constitutes 'adequate' mitigation; acceptance
      criteria and observable pass/fail oracle are missing.
    evidence_signals:
    - config_check
    - log_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0003-cedd2104
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: ineffective mitigation due to unconsidered interactions
  conditions:
  - combined application of the requirements set out in this Section
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - developer shall give due consideration to the effects and possible interaction
    resulting from the combined application of the requirements set out in this Section,
    with a view to minimising risks and achieving an appropriate balance in implementing
    the measures to fulfil those requirements.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Vague, subjective 'give due consideration' to unspecified interactions;
      no concrete measurable criteria or observable artifacts (io/log/config/ci/data/repo).
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0003-72c236f4
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: lack of required information for safe deployment
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - developer shall provide to deployers the information required pursuant to Article
    13.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Verify developer provided Article 13 required information by inspecting
      repository or deployment/configuration artifacts.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0003-168436c1
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: insufficient deployer preparedness
  conditions:
  - where appropriate
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - developer shall provide training to deployers where appropriate.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Conditional 'where appropriate' and no objective criteria or required
      artifacts to verify training; lacks observable pass/fail signals.
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0001-9f03494d
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0001
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: insufficient risk management measures
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - developer shall test high-risk AI systems for the purpose of identifying the most
    appropriate and targeted risk management measures.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Obligatory testing can be checked via CI/test reports or repository test
      artifacts.
    evidence_signals:
    - ci_gate
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0001-3957b413
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0001
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: inconsistent system performance
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - developer shall conduct testing that demonstrates high-risk AI systems perform
    consistently for their intended purpose.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: No objective acceptance criteria or measurable metrics defined to determine
      'consistent' performance.
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0001-5abd1480
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0001
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: non-compliance with Section requirements
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - developer shall conduct testing that demonstrates high-risk AI systems are in
    compliance with the requirements set out in this Section.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: No specific acceptance criteria, required artifacts, or pass/fail tests
      are defined to objectively verify compliance.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
    - ci_gate
    - io_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-bf5323e8
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - dev
  hazard: deployment of untested high-risk AI
  conditions:
  - at any time throughout the development process
  - prior to being placed on the market or put into service
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider shall perform testing of high-risk AI systems during development and,
    in any event, prior to placing them on the market or putting them into service.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Obligatory testing before market; verifiable via CI/test reports, runtime
      logs, or repository test artifacts.
    evidence_signals:
    - ci_gate
    - log_check
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-6c3b3957
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - dev
  hazard: incorrect performance due to inadequate validation against intended-purpose
    metrics
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider shall carry out testing against prior defined metrics and probabilistic
    thresholds that are appropriate to the intended purpose of the high-risk AI system.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Requires providers to perform tests against prior-defined metrics and
      thresholds; verifiable via metrics configs, test reports/CI gates, and execution
      logs.
    evidence_signals:
    - config_check
    - ci_gate
    - log_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-764e8798
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: adverse impact on persons under the age of 18 and other vulnerable groups
  conditions:
  - when implementing the risk management system as provided for in paragraphs 1 to
    7
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider shall give consideration to whether, in view of its intended purpose,
    the high-risk AI system is likely to have an adverse impact on persons under the
    age of 18 and, as appropriate, other vulnerable groups when implementing the risk
    management system.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: '''Give consideration'' is vague and lacks a specific, inspectable artifact
      or measurable criterion for objective pass/fail.'
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0003-26360280
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: use of datasets that do not meet required quality criteria
  conditions:
  - whenever training, validation and testing data sets are used
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - developer shall develop high-risk AI systems that make use of techniques involving
    the training of AI models on the basis of training, validation and testing data
    sets that meet the quality criteria referred to in paragraphs 2 to 5.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Requires developers to use training/validation/test datasets meeting specified
      quality criteria; dataset contents/metadata can be inspected for compliance.
    evidence_signals:
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0003-9a65d83c
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: inadequate data governance for intended purpose
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - developer shall subject training, validation and testing data sets to data governance
    and management practices that are appropriate for the intended purpose of the
    high-risk AI system.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Requirement is vague—'appropriate' practices unspecified; no objective
      predicate or artifact to determine compliance.
    evidence_signals:
    - data_check
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0003-698bb7c9
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: bias leading to harm, rights impact, or discrimination
  conditions:
  - especially where data outputs influence inputs for future operations
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - developer shall ensure data governance practices include examination for possible
    biases that are likely to affect the health and safety of persons, have a negative
    impact on fundamental rights or lead to discrimination prohibited under Union
    law.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Obligates developers to include bias examinations in data governance;
      presence can be checked in governance policies or documentation.
    evidence_signals:
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0003-d0de453e
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: insufficient data availability, quantity or suitability
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - developer shall ensure data governance practices include an assessment of the
    availability, quantity and suitability of the data sets that are needed.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Check for documented data-assessment artifacts or policy/config entries
      and dataset metadata evidencing availability, quantity, and suitability.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
    - config_check
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0003-ca5336a1
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: non-compliance due to data gaps or shortcomings
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - developer shall ensure data governance practices identify relevant data gaps or
    shortcomings that prevent compliance with this Regulation and specify how those
    gaps and shortcomings can be addressed.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Determining whether gaps ‘prevent compliance’ requires subjective judgment;
      artifact presence alone is insufficient for objective pass/fail.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0004-6e075e49
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0004
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0004
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: misaligned model behavior due to irrelevant training data
  conditions:
  - in view of the intended purpose
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Document that training, validation and testing data sets are relevant to the intended
    purpose.
  evidence:
  - dataset documentation (relevance assessment)
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Obligation to document is verifiable by inspecting repository/documentation
      for a statement that datasets are relevant to the intended purpose.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0004-aff77f49
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0004
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0004
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: biased outcomes due to unrepresentative data
  conditions:
  - in view of the intended purpose
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Ensure and record that training, validation and testing data sets are sufficiently
    representative for the intended purpose.
  evidence:
  - dataset documentation (representativeness metrics)
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Vague criterion—'sufficiently representative' lacks objective metrics
      or thresholds, so pass/fail cannot be verified via logs, configs, or data.
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0004-ddb15bfa
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0004
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0004
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: inaccurate model behavior due to erroneous or incomplete data
  conditions:
  - in view of the intended purpose
  - to the best extent possible
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Perform data quality checks and document that training, validation and testing
    data sets are, to the best extent possible, free of errors and complete in view
    of the intended purpose.
  evidence:
  - dataset documentation (data quality checks)
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Uses vague/subjective criteria ('to the best extent possible', 'complete
      in view of intended purpose'), so no objective pass/fail oracle
    evidence_signals:
    - data_check
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0004-838898b6
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0004
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/high-risk-ai-systems-shall-be-tested-for-the-purpose-of-iden/sent_0004
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: disparate impact on persons or groups due to inadequate statistical properties
  conditions:
  - in view of the intended purpose
  - where applicable, as regards the persons or groups of persons in relation to whom
    the high-risk AI system is intended to be used
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Assess and document that training, validation and testing data sets have appropriate
    statistical properties, including where applicable with respect to persons or
    groups for whom the high-risk AI system is intended to be used.
  evidence:
  - dataset documentation (statistical property analysis)
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Requires judging ‘appropriate statistical properties’ without defined
      metrics, so no objective pass/fail oracle.
    evidence_signals:
    - data_check
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0001-af4060e2
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0001
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain:
    - PII
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: unauthorized access or misuse of special categories of personal data
  conditions:
  - processing is strictly necessary for the purpose of ensuring bias detection and
    correction in relation to the high-risk AI systems in accordance with paragraph
    (2), points (f) and (g)
  - in addition to the provisions set out in Regulations (EU) 2016/679 and (EU) 2018/1725
    and Directive (EU) 2016/680
  - points (a) to (f) of paragraph 5 are met
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider shall not process special categories of personal data for the purpose
    of bias detection and correction unless the conditions listed in this rule are
    satisfied.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Exemption depends on unspecified "conditions listed in this rule", so
      compliance cannot be objectively checked from artifacts alone.
    evidence_signals:
    - data_check
    - log_check
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0001-9c6cc1b6
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0001
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain:
    - PII
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: unauthorized access or misuse of special categories of personal data
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider shall apply technical limitations on the re-use of the special categories
    of personal data and implement state-of-the-art security and privacy-preserving
    measures, including pseudonymisation.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: '''state-of-the-art'' and unspecified ''technical limitations'' are vague;
      no objective criterion/oracle to yield pass/fail.'
    evidence_signals:
    - data_check
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0001-cecc0146
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0001
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain:
    - PII
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: unauthorized retention of special categories of personal data beyond need
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider shall delete the special categories of personal data once the bias has
    been corrected or the personal data has reached the end of its retention period,
    whichever comes first.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Trigger "bias has been corrected" lacks an objective artifact; timing
      of required deletion cannot be deterministically verified.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - data_check
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0001-cfee8dc3
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0001
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain:
    - PII
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: lack of justification for processing special categories of personal data
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider shall ensure that the records of processing activities pursuant to Regulations
    (EU) 2016/679 and (EU) 2018/1725 and Directive (EU) 2016/680 include the reasons
    why the processing of special categories of personal data was strictly necessary
    to detect and correct biases and why that objective could not be achieved by processing
    other data.
  evidence:
  - records of processing activities
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: RoPA documents are inspectable; presence of the required justification
      fields can be objectively checked in records.
    evidence_signals:
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-96145790
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: deployment without required technical documentation
  conditions:
  - before that system is placed on the market or put into service
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - org shall draw up the technical documentation of a high-risk AI system before
    that system is placed on the market or put into service.
  evidence:
  - technical documentation
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Obligation to create technical documentation before market/service; verify
      by checking documentation artifacts and creation/deployment timestamps in repos
      or deployment logs.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
    - log_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-29fb8928
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: outdated technical documentation leading to unverifiable compliance
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - org shall keep the technical documentation of a high-risk AI system up-to-date.
  evidence:
  - technical documentation
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Vague 'up-to-date' requirement lacks an objective metric (frequency/content),
      so no deterministic pass/fail via artifacts.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
    - log_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-b04bdd0f
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: regulatory non-compliance due to insufficient evidence of conformity
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - org shall draw up the technical documentation so that it demonstrates that the
    high-risk AI system complies with the requirements set out in this Section.
  evidence:
  - technical documentation
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: '''Demonstrates compliance'' is subjective; no objective pass/fail criterion
      or single oracle specified to verify conformity.'
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
    - config_check
    - io_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-a9a98020
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: inability of authorities to assess compliance
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - org shall ensure the technical documentation provides national competent authorities
    and notified bodies with the necessary information in a clear and comprehensive
    form to assess the compliance of the AI system with those requirements.
  evidence:
  - technical documentation
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: No objective criteria for "necessary" information or "clear and comprehensive";
      cannot automatically verify documentation contents.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-6ca84a97
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: missing required Annex IV documentation elements
  conditions:
  - elements set out in Annex IV
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - org shall ensure the technical documentation contains, at a minimum, the elements
    set out in Annex IV.
  evidence:
  - technical documentation
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Obligation to include Annex IV elements in technical documentation; verifiable
      by inspecting documentation artifacts (repo/files) for required elements.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0003-aa55a3e4
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: non-conformity with Annex IV technical documentation requirements
  conditions:
  - opts to provide the information required in Annex IV in a simplified manner
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - When an SME, including a start-up, opts to provide the information required in
    Annex IV in a simplified manner, the org shall use the simplified technical documentation
    form referred to in this paragraph.
  evidence:
  - technical documentation (Annex IV)
  - simplified technical documentation form
  severity: medium
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Specifies an obligation to use a particular form when SMEs opt for simplified
      Annex IV; verifiable by inspecting submitted documentation files.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0003-2a6aa1d0
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - auditor
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: rejection of the simplified technical documentation form during conformity
    assessment
  conditions:
  - for the purposes of the conformity assessment
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Auditor shall accept the simplified technical documentation form referred to in
    this paragraph for the purposes of the conformity assessment.
  evidence:
  - simplified technical documentation form
  severity: medium
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Obligates auditors to accept a specific document during conformity assessment;
      verifiable by inspecting audit decision records or logs showing acceptance.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0004-7b262c87
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0004
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0004
  scope:
    actor:
    - deployer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: missing required technical documentation
  conditions:
  - high-risk AI system
  - related to a product covered by Union harmonisation legislation listed in Section
    A of Annex I
  - placed on the market or put into service
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Draw up a single set of technical documentation when the conditions apply.
  evidence:
  - technical documentation
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Requires deployer to produce one technical documentation set for high-risk
      cases; presence/uniqueness of doc files in repo is checkable.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0001-c048ac64
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: article-12/sent_0001
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/article-12/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: insufficient event traceability
  conditions:
  - over the lifetime of the system
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Developer shall technically implement automatic recording of events (logs) for
    the high-risk AI system that operates over the lifetime of the system.
  evidence:
  - logs
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Obligation to implement automatic event logging; verifiable by inspecting
      runtime logs or logging configuration.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0001-a44fc60f
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: article-12/sent_0001
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/article-12/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: insufficient traceability for detection, monitoring, and post-market review
  conditions:
  - appropriate to the intended purpose of the system
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Developer shall enable logging to record events relevant for identifying situations
    that may result in the high-risk AI system presenting a risk within the meaning
    of Article 79(1) or in a substantial modification.
  evidence:
  - logs
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: ‘Events relevant for identifying…’ is undefined, making pass/fail subjective
      rather than objectively verifiable.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0001-4bdef0e2
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: article-12/sent_0001
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/article-12/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: insufficient traceability for detection, monitoring, and post-market review
  conditions:
  - appropriate to the intended purpose of the system
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Developer shall enable logging to record events relevant for facilitating the
    post-market monitoring referred to in Article 72.
  evidence:
  - logs
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Obligation lacks a concrete, verifiable list of "relevant events", so
      pass/fail cannot be determined objectively.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0001-8902f308
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: article-12/sent_0001
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/article-12/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: missing records of system use periods
  conditions:
  - Annex III point 1(a) system
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Developer shall ensure logging capabilities provide recording of the period of
    each use of the system, including start date and time and end date and time of
    each use.
  evidence:
  - logs
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Logs can be inspected to confirm each system-use period has start and
      end date/time entries.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0001-d786b428
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: article-12/sent_0001
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/article-12/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: lack of traceability to reference data sources
  conditions:
  - Annex III point 1(a) system
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Developer shall ensure logging capabilities record the reference database against
    which input data has been checked by the system.
  evidence:
  - logs
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Logs can be inspected to verify entries include the reference database
      identifier; logging configuration can also be checked.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0001-498aa0b8
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: article-12/sent_0001
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/article-12/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: inability to trace matched input data
  conditions:
  - Annex III point 1(a) system
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Developer shall ensure logging capabilities record the input data for which the
    search has led to a match.
  evidence:
  - logs
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Obligation to log matched input can be verified by inspecting runtime
      logs for entries recording input data when a search yields a match.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0001-860fcf38
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: article-12/sent_0001
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/article-12/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: unattributed human verification of results
  conditions:
  - Annex III point 1(a) system
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Developer shall ensure logging capabilities record the identification of the natural
    persons involved in the verification of the results, as referred to in Article
    14(5).
  evidence:
  - logs
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Logs or logging configuration can be inspected to verify entries record
      identifiers of natural persons who verified results.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-6f182111
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: article-12/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/article-12/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: misinterpretation of outputs leading to inappropriate use
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The developer shall design and develop high-risk AI systems so that their operation
    is sufficiently transparent to enable deployers to interpret the system's output
    and use it appropriately.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Vague "sufficiently transparent" lacks measurable criteria or specific
      artifacts; no oracle can objectively verify compliance.
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-fbf2c6a0
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: article-12/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/article-12/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: non-compliance with provider and deployer obligations due to insufficient
    transparency
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The developer shall ensure an appropriate type and degree of transparency in high-risk
    AI systems with a view to achieving compliance with the relevant obligations of
    the provider and deployer set out in Section 3.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Vague 'appropriate type and degree of transparency' lacks measurable criteria
      to verify compliance.
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-b44ba33c
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: article-12/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/article-12/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: deployers unable to use system due to unclear or incomplete instructions
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The org shall accompany high-risk AI systems with instructions for use in an appropriate
    digital format or otherwise that include concise, complete, correct and clear
    information that is relevant, accessible and comprehensible to deployers.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Qualitative attributes (concise/complete/correct/clear/relevant/accessible/comprehensible)
      lack objective pass/fail criteria.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
    - io_check
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0003-04fd6e79
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: article-12/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/article-12/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: inability to contact provider
  conditions: []
  exceptions:
  - where applicable, authorised representative
  requirements:
  - The org shall include in the instructions for use the identity and the contact
    details of the provider and, where applicable, of its authorised representative.
  evidence:
  - instructions for use
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Inspect instructions-for-use documentation (repo/docs) to verify provider
      identity and contact details, and authorised representative when applicable.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0003-d9b4dd6f
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: article-12/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/article-12/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: use outside intended purpose
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The org shall include in the instructions for use the intended purpose of the
    high-risk AI system.
  evidence:
  - instructions for use
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Inspect the instructions-for-use document (repo/config) to verify it explicitly
      states the system's intended purpose.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0003-61a749d4
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: article-12/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/article-12/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: reduced accuracy, robustness or cybersecurity
  conditions:
  - referred to in Article 15
  - against which the high-risk AI system has been tested and validated
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The org shall include in the instructions for use the level of accuracy, including
    its metrics, robustness and cybersecurity referred to in Article 15 against which
    the high-risk AI system has been tested and validated and which can be expected,
    and any known and foreseeable circumstances that may have an impact on that expected
    level of accuracy, robustness and cybersecurity.
  evidence:
  - instructions for use
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Mandated content in 'instructions for use' is inspectable in product documentation/repository;
      presence and specific statements can be verified.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0003-157d81f5
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: article-12/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/article-12/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: risks to health
  conditions:
  - in accordance with its intended purpose or under conditions of reasonably foreseeable
    misuse
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The org shall include in the instructions for use any known or foreseeable circumstance,
    related to the use of the high-risk AI system in accordance with its intended
    purpose or under conditions of reasonably foreseeable misuse, which may lead to
    risks to health.
  evidence:
  - instructions for use
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Completeness of 'known or foreseeable' circumstances is subjective and
      requires risk‑assessment artifacts not specified.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0001-d08646aa
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0001
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: insufficient human oversight
  conditions:
  - during the period in which they are in use
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Developer shall design and develop the high-risk AI system with appropriate human-machine
    interface tools that enable effective oversight by natural persons during the
    period in which the system is in use.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Obligation is vague—'appropriate' interfaces and 'effective oversight'
      lack measurable criteria; no objective oracle can determine pass/fail.
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0001-61f80f2e
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0001
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: risks to health, safety or fundamental rights
  conditions:
  - when the system is used in accordance with its intended purpose or under conditions
    of reasonably foreseeable misuse
  - in particular where such risks persist despite the application of other requirements
    set out in this Section
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Developer shall implement human oversight measures that aim to prevent or minimise
    risks to health, safety or fundamental rights arising during intended use or under
    reasonably foreseeable misuse.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Requirement is vague—no specific, observable artifacts or metrics to verify
      oversight measures' existence or effectiveness against listed risks.
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-e972a467
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: insufficient human oversight
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The provider shall ensure that oversight measures are commensurate with the risks,
    level of autonomy and context of use of the high-risk AI system.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: '''Commensurate with the risks'' is subjective and lacks measurable thresholds
      or concrete criteria for objective verification.'
    evidence_signals:
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-ce818cdd
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: missing built-in oversight measures
  conditions:
  - when technically feasible
  - before it is placed on the market or put into service
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The provider shall identify and build measures into the high-risk AI system, when
    technically feasible, before it is placed on the market or put into service.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: 'Vague obligation: ''measures'' and ''technically feasible'' lack concrete
      criteria or artifacts for objective pass/fail.'
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-52d34771
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: insufficient deployer-implementable oversight measures
  conditions:
  - before placing on the market or putting into service
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The provider shall identify, before placing the high-risk AI system on the market
    or putting it into service, measures that are appropriate to be implemented by
    the deployer.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Requires identification of “appropriate” measures — appropriateness is
      subjective and lacks an objective oracle to verify compliance.
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-00407898
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: undetected anomalies or dysfunctions due to inadequate oversight
  conditions:
  - when the high-risk AI system is provided to the deployer
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The provider shall provide the high-risk AI system to the deployer in such a way
    that natural persons to whom human oversight is assigned are enabled to properly
    understand the system's relevant capacities and limitations and be able to duly
    monitor its operation, including detecting and addressing anomalies, dysfunctions
    and unexpected performance.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: No objective measurable criteria (e.g., 'properly', 'duly'); pass/fail
      cannot be determined from I/O, logs, or configs.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-8e0ff5e7
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: automation bias (over-reliance on system outputs)
  conditions:
  - in particular for high-risk AI systems used to provide information or recommendations
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The provider shall provide the high-risk AI system to the deployer in such a way
    that natural persons to whom human oversight is assigned are enabled to remain
    aware of the possible tendency to automatically rely or over-rely on the output
    produced by the high-risk AI system.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: '''enabled to remain aware'' is vague and lacks a concrete, objectively
      verifiable artifact or metric for pass/fail.'
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0001-49441479
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: the-output-of-the-high-risk-ai-system/sent_0001
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/the-output-of-the-high-risk-ai-system/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - deployer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: action based on unverified identification
  conditions:
  - Annex III point 1(a) system
  - based on the identification resulting from the system
  - identification separately verified and confirmed by at least two natural persons
    with the necessary competence, training and authority
  exceptions:
  - where used for law enforcement, migration, border control or asylum and Union
    or national law considers the application of this requirement disproportionate
  requirements:
  - The deployer shall not take any action or decision based on the identification
    resulting from the system unless that identification has been separately verified
    and confirmed by at least two natural persons with the necessary competence, training
    and authority.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Verify logs/configs show two distinct authorized human confirmations before
      any deployer action based on system identification.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-0d4ec897
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: the-output-of-the-high-risk-ai-system/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/the-output-of-the-high-risk-ai-system/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: insufficient accuracy
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The developer shall design and develop high-risk AI systems to achieve an appropriate
    level of accuracy.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: 'Vague requirement: ''appropriate level of accuracy'' lacks measurable
      metric or threshold, so no objective pass/fail oracle.'
    evidence_signals:
    - config_check
    - io_check
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-bc6a4593
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: the-output-of-the-high-risk-ai-system/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/the-output-of-the-high-risk-ai-system/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: cybersecurity vulnerabilities
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The developer shall design and develop high-risk AI systems to achieve an appropriate
    level of cybersecurity.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Vague/unbounded obligation — 'appropriate level of cybersecurity' lacks
      measurable criteria or observable predicates for objective pass/fail verification.
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-06bedd55
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: the-output-of-the-high-risk-ai-system/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/the-output-of-the-high-risk-ai-system/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: performance degradation over lifecycle
  conditions:
  - throughout their lifecycle
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The developer shall design and develop high-risk AI systems so that they perform
    consistently in accuracy, robustness and cybersecurity throughout their lifecycle.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Vague 'perform consistently' lacks measurable metrics, thresholds, timeframe
      or an objective pass/fail predicate.
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-8e58b876
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: the-output-of-the-high-risk-ai-system/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/the-output-of-the-high-risk-ai-system/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: unhandled errors or faults due to interactions
  conditions:
  - regarding errors, faults or inconsistencies that may occur within the system or
    the environment
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The developer shall design and develop high-risk AI systems to be as resilient
    as possible to errors, faults or inconsistencies, in particular those due to interaction
    with natural persons or other systems.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Vague, unquantified "as resilient as possible" obligation lacks measurable
      criteria or artifacts; no oracle can determine pass/fail.
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-caf0277c
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: the-output-of-the-high-risk-ai-system/sent_0002
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/the-output-of-the-high-risk-ai-system/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: undisclosed accuracy metrics
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The org shall declare the levels of accuracy and the relevant accuracy metrics
    of high-risk AI systems in the accompanying instructions of use.
  evidence: []
  severity: medium
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Verify documentation contains declared accuracy levels and metrics by
      inspecting accompanying instructions (repo/config files).
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0003-30745643
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: the-output-of-the-high-risk-ai-system/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/the-output-of-the-high-risk-ai-system/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: bias amplification via feedback loops
  conditions:
  - that continue to learn after being placed on the market or put into service
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - developer shall develop high-risk AI systems that continue to learn after being
    placed on the market or put into service to eliminate or reduce as far as possible
    the risk of possibly biased outputs influencing input for future operations (feedback
    loops).
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Mandates reducing bias 'as far as possible' without a defined metric or
      objective pass/fail; outcome not objectively verifiable.
    evidence_signals:
    - config_check
    - log_check
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0003-ecca1ccf
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: the-output-of-the-high-risk-ai-system/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/the-output-of-the-high-risk-ai-system/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: bias amplification via feedback loops
  conditions:
  - that continue to learn after being placed on the market or put into service
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - developer shall ensure that any feedback loops resulting from continued learning
    after market placement or being put into service are duly addressed with appropriate
    mitigation measures.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Vague requirement ('appropriate mitigation measures') lacks objective
      pass/fail criteria; no clear observable oracle to verify compliance.
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0003-e15eb233
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: the-output-of-the-high-risk-ai-system/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/the-output-of-the-high-risk-ai-system/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorised alteration of system use, outputs or performance by exploiting
    vulnerabilities
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - org shall ensure high-risk AI systems are resilient against attempts by unauthorised
    third parties to alter their use, outputs or performance by exploiting system
    vulnerabilities.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Vague 'resilient' obligation lacks measurable acceptance criteria or concrete
      artifacts to enable an objective pass/fail oracle.
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0003-9b3c60e8
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: the-output-of-the-high-risk-ai-system/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/the-output-of-the-high-risk-ai-system/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: unmitigated feedback loops
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - org shall take technical and organisational measures in relation to the risks
    described in this clause.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Vague obligation lacking specific measures, metrics, or observable artifacts;
      no objective oracle can verify compliance.
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0004-1ff28756
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: the-output-of-the-high-risk-ai-system/sent_0004
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/the-output-of-the-high-risk-ai-system/sent_0004
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: insufficient cybersecurity
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - org shall ensure that the technical solutions aiming to ensure the cybersecurity
    of high-risk AI systems are appropriate to the relevant circumstances and the
    risks.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Vague requirement — “appropriate to circumstances and the risks” has no
      measurable criteria or observable predicates to check objectively.
    evidence_signals:
